**Code Explanation:**

This script generates all 5 figures for the superdiffusion analysis. It computes all required quantities from scratch using imported functions, loads CF fit results from Step 2 npz files, and produces publication-quality figures saved to data/. All key numerical results are printed to the console. Units: positions in m, time in s, MSD in m^2, D_alpha in m^alpha/s, EB dimensionless. Helper functions include: get_ensemble_tamsd (computes ensemble-averaged TAMSD and per-tracer matrices), fit_powerlaw_range (performs power-law fits on TAMSD), compute_displacement_pdf_logbins (computes displacement PDFs with log-spaced bins), and fit_tail_powerlaw (estimates tail exponents).

